<paragraph blockId="67.[151,908,263,319]" box="[151,476,296,319]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Number of (Recent) species: 1</paragraph>
<caption pageId="67" pageNumber="68" startId="67.[151,255,1593,1617]" targetBox="[164,1417,388,1551]" targetPageId="67">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,1593,1688]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,1593,1617]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">FIGURE 31.</emphasis>
SEM micrographs of chaetae in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="de Montfort" baseAuthorityYear="1808" box="[656,854,1593,1616]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Nogrobs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="grimaldii">
<emphasis box="[656,854,1593,1616]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Nogrobs grimaldii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Azores, 39°03.5' N, 28°25.5' W, 2440 m, R/V “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Jean Charcot</emphasis>
”, det. H. Zibrowius 1972, ZMA V.Pol. 3906. A—collar chaetae, B—6 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1025,1036,1628,1641]" fontSize="5" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">th</superScript>
row of thoracic uncini, C—anterior abdominal uncini, D—anterior abdominal chaeta.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1436,1735,2031]" lastBlockId="68.[151,1436,152,719]" lastPageId="68" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Tube free, white, sinistrally coiled, initially cylindrical, then prismatic (quadrangular in cross-section), finally with short cylindrical straight distal part. Collar like rings and granular overlay absent. Operculum inverse cone (ampulla) with chitinous endplate and central depression. Peduncle pinnulated, without distal wings, with outer groove distally, with or without constriction beneath ampulla; inserted as second right radiole, up to 3 times as wide as other radioles. Pseudoperculum absent. Arrangement of radioles semi-circular, up to 8 per lobe. Inter-radiolar membrane, branchial eyes, and stylodes absent. Mouth palps absent. 4–6 thoracic chaetigerous segments. Collar non-lobed with entire edge, no clear separation towards thoracic membranes that end at second chaetiger. No apron, no tonguelets. Collar chaetae limbate (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1199,2005,2031]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[151,255,1593,1617]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,388,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-199@67.[151,1436,373,1569]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Nogrobs grimaldii. Azores, 39°03.5' N, 28°25.5' W, 2440 m, R/V “Jean Charcot”, det. H. Zibrowius 1972, ZMA V.Pol. 3906. A—collar chaetae, B—6th row of thoracic uncini, C—anterior abdominal uncini, D—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 31A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[1221,1338,2005,2030]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1338,2005,2030]" italics="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
chaetae absent. Thoracic uncini saw-to-rasp-shaped with numerous teeth (&gt; 12) in profile, 2–3 teeth per row (dental formula P:3:3:3:2:2:1:1:1:1:1:1:1:1); anterior peg gouged (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[842,995,191,216]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Pomatoceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[842,995,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Pomatoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[1003,1055,190,216]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">type</typeStatus>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1080,1187,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[151,255,1593,1617]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,388,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-199@67.[151,1436,373,1569]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Nogrobs grimaldii. Azores, 39°03.5' N, 28°25.5' W, 2440 m, R/V “Jean Charcot”, det. H. Zibrowius 1972, ZMA V.Pol. 3906. A—collar chaetae, B—6th row of thoracic uncini, C—anterior abdominal uncini, D—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 31B</figureCitation>
). Abdominal chaetae short, with flat triangular denticulate blade (
<figureCitation box="[692,806,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[151,255,1593,1617]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,388,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-199@67.[151,1436,373,1569]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Nogrobs grimaldii. Azores, 39°03.5' N, 28°25.5' W, 2440 m, R/V “Jean Charcot”, det. H. Zibrowius 1972, ZMA V.Pol. 3906. A—collar chaetae, B—6th row of thoracic uncini, C—anterior abdominal uncini, D—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 31D</figureCitation>
). Thoracic triangular depression absent. Abdominal uncini similar to thoracic ones (
<figureCitation box="[518,625,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 31" captionStartId="67.[151,255,1593,1617]" captionTargetBox="[164,1417,388,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-199@67.[151,1436,373,1569]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 31. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Nogrobs grimaldii. Azores, 39°03.5' N, 28°25.5' W, 2440 m, R/V “Jean Charcot”, det. H. Zibrowius 1972, ZMA V.Pol. 3906. A—collar chaetae, B—6th row of thoracic uncini, C—anterior abdominal uncini, D—anterior abdominal chaeta." pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Fig. 31C</figureCitation>
). Achaetous anterior abdominal zone absent. Long posterior capillary chaetae absent. Posterior glandular pad absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="68" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1436,152,719]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,344,370]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Remarks.</emphasis>
The diagnosis above is based on the description of the only Recent species thus far described - from specimens collected at depths of 
<quantity box="[621,787,384,410]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.873" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.846" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="m" value="1873.0" valueMax="1900.0" valueMin="1846.0">1846–1900 m</quantity>
off the 
<collectingRegion box="[888,975,384,410]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Azores</collectingRegion>
. Topotypical material from 
<quantity box="[1313,1406,384,410]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.44" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="m" value="2440.0">2440 m</quantity>
is present in the collections of the ZMA (V.Pol. 3906, presented by H. Zibrowius), additional material from the Central Atlantic was mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O. &amp; Fauchald, K." box="[567,903,461,487]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 327" refId="ref60039" refString="Hartman, O. &amp; Fauchald, K. (1971). Deep-water benthic polychaetous annelids off New England to Bermuda and other North Atlantic areas. Part 2. Allan Hancock Monographs in Marine Biology, 6, 1 - 327." type="journal article" year="1971">Hartman &amp; Fauchald (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, they, however, counted 4 thoracic chaetigers only. A possible second undescribed species was found at 
<quantity box="[833,922,500,526]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.124" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" unit="m" value="4124.0">4124 m</quantity>
south-east off the 
<collectingRegion box="[1139,1353,500,526]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Galapagos Islands</collectingRegion>
(ZMA V.Pol. 3859). Zibrowius (pers. comm.) suspects a total of 4 different species, partly with not coiled quadrangular tubes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="68.[151,1436,152,719]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">
<bibRefCitation author="Jager, M." box="[198,352,616,642]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="121 - 249" refId="ref62313" refString="Jager, M. (2004) Serpulidae und Spirorbidae (Polychaeta sedentaria) aus Campan und Maastricht von Norddeutschland, den Niederlanden, Belgien und angrenzenden Gebieten. Geologisches Jahrbuch, A 157, 121 - 249." type="journal article" year="2004">Jäger (2004)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized the Recent genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fauvel, 1909" authorityName="Fauvel" authorityYear="1909" box="[767,1077,616,642]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Spirodiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[767,902,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Spirodiscus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." box="[917,1077,616,642]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref58340" refString="Fauvel, P. (1909) Deuxieme note preliminaire sur les Polychetes provenant des campagnes de l'Hirondelle et de la Princesse-Alice, ou deposees dans la Musee Oceanographique de Monaco. Bulletin de l'Institute Oceanographique, 142, 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1909">Fauvel, 1909</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with the Fossil 
<taxonomicName authority="de Montfort, 1808" authorityName="de Montfort" authorityYear="1808" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Nogrobs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1294,1394,616,641]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Nogrobs</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation author="Montfort, D. de" box="[151,339,654,680]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" refId="ref64407" refString="Montfort, D. de (1808) Conchyliologie systematique, 1. Coquilles univalves, cloisonees. Paris, lxxxvii + 409 pp." type="book" year="1808">Montfort, 1808</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Jäger also suggested that the Recent 
<taxonomicName box="[822,1053,655,680]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Bathyditrupa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hovei">
<emphasis box="[822,1053,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Bathyditrupa hovei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might belong to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Regenhardt, 1961" authorityName="Regenhardt" authorityYear="1961" box="[151,642,693,719]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Nogrobs" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" phylum="Annelida" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Tetraditrupa">
<emphasis box="[151,251,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Nogrobs</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[268,415,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Tetraditrupa</emphasis>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Regenhardt, H." box="[432,642,693,719]" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" pagination="5 - 115" refId="ref66404" refString="Regenhardt, H. (1961) Serpulidae (Polychaeta sedentaria) aus der Kreide Mitteleuropas, ihre okologische, taxionomische und stratigraphische Bewertung. Mitteilungen aus dem Geologischen Staatsinstitut in Hamburg, 30, 5 - 115." type="journal article" year="1961">Regenhardt, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, without further argumentation.
</paragraph>
